programme.desc: Stephanie is an avid soccer player, but she doesn't get much of a kick out of life anymore. Stephanie's worst fear about her appearance is her teeth, or rather her missing tooth and she also thinks her skin is aging prematurely.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: The Most Revealing Reveal Ever
programme.desc: After years of sunbathing, Stefanie hid her sun-damaged skin under frumpy and matronly clothes. But after a flurry of skin treatments, Stefanie stuns her family and friends at one of our most revealing reveals ever!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: A Budding New Look
programme.desc: When Rose was growing up, she was called "the ugliest girl" at her high school. Even though she is now grown up and has a loving fiancé, those cruel comments from her past still haunt her.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand: Jason Searell
programme.desc: Jason Searell admits he's let himself go, and he's gone a long way. Jason needs a complete overhaul but can Fiona McDonald and her team of experts really knock off 10 years in just 10 days?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: A Fresh Start
programme.desc: Dawn was sexually assaulted at the age of 16. Decades later, she's still missing her two front teeth as a result of the violent assault – a constant reminder of the pain and suffering she experienced.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: All Boys to All Glamour
programme.desc: Patty is a busy mom, shuttling the kids to school and basketball games. In a house with three boys, a husband and even a male dog, Patty's girl-time gets lost in the shuffle. The Glam Squad and our doctors are going to give Patty some time for herself.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Sharon Evans "One Year On"
programme.desc: Sharon Evans was one of the most breath-taking transformations of last series. Has Sharon managed to ditch the floral body warner forever or slipped back in to her old ways?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand: Jo Imrie
programme.desc: Jo Imrie refuses to exercise, smokes like a chimney, and has stopped caring about fashion. Recently mistaken for a granny she wants to change and desperately needs the help of Fiona McDonald and her team of experts. But are they up to the challenge?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand: Pam Coils
programme.desc: Recently graduated, Pam Coils is after her perfect job. But unfortunately, first impressions count and Pam thinks she makes a bad one. With the help of a team of experts, Fiona McDonald aims to roll back the years and inject Pam with some self-confidence.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Eileen Breading
programme.desc: 48 year old Eileen Breading from Peterborough used to live life in the fast lane. However, nine years ago she gave up the high life, choosing instead to care for her elderly mother full time. Cue Nicky Hambleton-Jones and her expert team.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Age Defense
programme.desc: Katie is a stay-at-home mom who put her own aspirations on hold for her husband and kids, but now she's ready to start fresh. After a little cosmetic tweaking to perfect her smile and high-tech dermatology to help her skin, she's ready to strike back.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 1
programme.desc: New Year's Eve at Leopard's Den. Alice has returned, but the stress of combining work with caring for baby Bobby is causing tension between her and Danny. Liv is furious that Fatani hasn't told his mother about their relationship.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Scabby Monkey
programme.desc: Contending with overweight cats and their over protective owners was not what Danny Trevanion had in mind when he became a vet. So when a scruffy, barely alive African monkey arrives at his practise Danny is fascinated by the challenge.

programme.title: Wild At Heart
programme.desc: Danny is having second thoughts about the wisdom of uprooting his new family and ploughing all their money into a business venture that they know next to nothing about.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Work To Do
programme.desc: A successful giraffe capture means everyone is in high spirits, until the arrival of Evan and Olivia's real father, Simon, throws the family into turmoil.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Meerly Evan
programme.desc: Evan lets the mischievous meerkats loose in Rosie's room to cause havoc. Rosie is devastated when they destroy an irreplaceable photograph of her mother and rages at Evan. She decides once and for all to go back to Bristol.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Evan Meets Elli
programme.desc: Rogue young male elephants are rampaging through Leopard's Den and destroying everything the family have built, so Danny introduces a matriarch elephant in the hope that she will calm them down.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Dawn Feeling
programme.desc: At a typically rowdy family breakfast, Rosie is excitedly looking forward to the arrival of her friend Izzy, whilst Danny is concerned about the rumour of ivory poachers in the area. Unnoticed, Miranda the lion cub pads off into the bush.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 2
programme.desc: Fishing buddies Scott, Wayne and Wayne's son Andrew head out to their favorite fishing spot, but when a freak wave hits their boat they have no choice but to SOS for help. Within minutes, the boat capsizes. Can the Air Rescue crew get to them in time?

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 3
programme.desc: 71 year-old retired nurse Sandra was exploring Tasmania's Cradle Mountain when she slipped and fractured her wrist. She's in excruciating pain and night is falling. Visibility is dangerously low. Can the rescue team get in close enough to get them out?

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 1
programme.desc: The Rescue 1 chopper team struggles to save two young men who are feared drowned at Hahei; a Coromandel motorcyclist is struggling with punctured lungs, and young man is trapped inside a car after a high speed accident.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 2
programme.desc: A teenage motorcyclist is fighting for his life after crashing on a remote farm near Warkworth, a man has 2nd degree burns to his face and hands from an accidental explosion, and four men are missing after two boats capsized on the Kawhia bar.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 3
programme.desc: The Rescue 1 team battles to save a man trapped in his overturned Land Rover on Rakino Island; a star rugby player at Onewhero may have broken his neck after a scrum collapsed, and a man out cycling on Waiheke is clinging to life after a cardiac arrest.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 4
programme.desc: The chopper team has an intense struggle to keep a young Waikato woman alive after her car collided with a heavy truck, an 18 year old man is in terrible pain with a dislocated shoulder, and a 9 year old boy is in a bad way after falling out of a tree.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 5
programme.desc: The Westpac chopper crew attempt to save a Waiheke man who has life-threatening injuries after falling off a ladder and a motocross rider is in a bad way after a 100-foot jump goes badly wrong.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4
programme.desc: Mountain bike fanatic, Blake was out riding when he clipped a tree and crashed into a rock. It's a time critical rescue mission. And what the rescue crew doesn't yet know is that Blake is about to take a turn for the worse.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: Motorbike rider, Lachlan was testing out his newly designed dirt-bike track when he lost control on a jump. His femur has been badly shattered. The Air Rescue crew is tasked with flying Lachlan to hospital but his medical dramas have only just begun.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: Retirees Diane and husband Gary were just a few hours into their Pacific Island cruise of a lifetime when disaster struck. Diane toppled down a set of stairs and now she's in need of urgent medical attention.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 1
programme.desc: A leisure helicopter has gone down in Sydney's Royal National Park with a family of four on board, including three year-old Finn. The stakes are always high when children are involved. The rescue crew locates the crash site but can't get too close.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 2
programme.desc: Three surfing mates go missing in dangerous surf. The massive swell threatens to smash them onto the rocks in Sydney's Lurline Bay. The rescue crew is on a search and rescue mission but there's no sign of the surfer boys.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 6
programme.desc: The helicopter rescue crew responds to Pauanui to save a truck driver who's smashed through the windscreen after rolling his truck and a Port Charles family is distraught after a young girl is run over by a quad bike.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 7
programme.desc: The chopper crewmen have their hands full with five badly injured patients after a car crash near Waiuku, and a massive motorcycle pile-up leaves injured bikers all over the road, and a man may have broken his neck after falling from his horse.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 8
programme.desc: As a weather bomb hits, the chopper crew set out on one of the most challenging missions they have ever undertaken 20 miles off shore, a man lays face down at Muriwai beach unable to move.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Triumph Tiger 800 XC

programme.title: Motorheads: Ferry Porsche

programme.title: Motorheads: Walther Roehrl

programme.title: Motorheads: Hans-Joachim Stuck

programme.title: Motorheads: Stephane Peterhansel

programme.title: Motorheads: Alois Ruf

programme.title: Motorheads: Hans Herrmann

programme.title: Motorheads: Sabine Schmitz

programme.title: Motorheads: Prince Leopold von Bayern

programme.title: Motorheads: Henry Ford

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: One Taelon Avenue

programme.title: Tyler Perry's Assisted Living: Add More Color
programme.desc: Mr. Brown gives Sandra advice on how to get what she wants and her outfit for school. Sandra apologises to her parents. Leah grows concerned with Sandra's sudden change of heart. (S1, ep18)

programme.title: Tyler Perry's The Oval: Allies
programme.desc: Victoria seeks to put an end to Hunter's continued indiscretions.

programme.title: Tyler Perry's The Oval: Lab Rats
programme.desc: Sharon makes a decision that could sabotage the two relationships most important to her.

programme.title: Tyler Perry's The Oval: The Dark Sheep
programme.desc: Hunter's reckless behavior becomes uncontrollable.

programme.title: Tyler Perry's The Oval: Eye On The Sparrow
programme.desc: Gayle learns her actions have consequences outside the walls of the White House.

programme.title: Tyler Perry's The Oval: The Fish Bowl
programme.desc: Lilly fears she has been set up by diabolical foes.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Shape Shifter
programme.desc: PRS travels to Shapleigh, Maine where a woman and her daughter are reporting attacks from a winged creature with sharp teeth. Psychic Chip Coffey arrives and senses a half-human, half animal presence.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Ghost On the Tracks
programme.desc: PRS is called to a New Jersey beauty salon, but they soon learn that the building's proximity to deadly train tracks might be the true cause of spirit activity.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Permission To Do Harm
programme.desc: When a mirror levitates and shatters on its own, P.R.S. heeds the call to investigate a spirit that has been unleashed on an unsuspecting family. Ryan must track down the spirit and contain it before it does irreparable damage.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Fury
programme.desc: Kathy, her two daughters and her new husband, "Farmer" thought they had the perfect, quiet life deep in the mountains of West Virginia.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Smoke and Shadows
programme.desc: Sarah believes her Parkville, MD home has been invaded by a powerful force ever since her roommate Dennis moved in. PRS investigates claims that Dennis has been attacked by the entity, a possible poltergeist.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Do Bad Things
programme.desc: After receiving a letter requesting PRS' help, Ryan and the team head to Ohio to help a grieving family and determine if the family's house contributed to the untimely death of a daughter.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Dark Practice
programme.desc: Brenda is terrified by a dark hooded figure spotted in her West Virginia home. The same entity allegedly tormented her late husband. PRS and Psychic/Medium Michelle Belanger help Brenda before she slips into the same abyss as her late husband.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Anniversary
programme.desc: Ever since a close-knit Kentucky family moved into their new home, they've been visited by the spirit of a young girl.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Ghosts of the Forgotten
programme.desc: The PRS investigation into the haunted Lake County Poor House becomes a journey through one PRS team members? troubled past.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Haunted Ranch
programme.desc: PRS saddles up to a remote ranch in Hunt, Texas where black shadows are being spotted and animals harmed. What's more, a mysterious crop circle has formed on the property and the horses refuse to cross it.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Desperate Households
programme.desc: When Julie and her family moved into their dream home in suburban New Jersey they quickly realized they were not alone.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Haunted Connection
programme.desc: P.R.S. is called in to help a young mother tormented by an otherworldly connection to a teenage girl murdered in her neighborhood years ago. Could she have psychic ability or is there a more sinister force at work?

programme.title: Paranormal State: Church of the Damned
programme.desc: Jason and his family can no longer do renovations of an abandoned Kansas church, especially after they found their father in the basement crying and frightened because of the menacing activity.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Who Is the Lurking Man?
programme.desc: PRS travels to Newcastle, CA to investigate a house with paranormal forces so strong, the family has cleared out. Ryan believes the Native American land may hold the key to the mystery and leads the team in a fight to reclaim a scared family's house.

programme.title: Most Haunted: West Virginia State Penitentiary
programme.desc: Until 1995, the West Virginia Penitentiary held some gruesome inmates. The team investigates claims that some of its most violent inmates have hung around to terrorize anyone who enters their world.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Sleepy Hollow
programme.desc: One cannot say the words "Sleepy Hollow" without invoking the famous story of the Headless Horseman. The team heads down to the cemetery and sets up camp at the location of the infamous wooden bridge.

programme.title: Most Haunted: New London Ledge Lighthouse
programme.desc: The New London Ledge Lighthouse in Connecticut sets the investigation team adrift as it isolates them for an entire night of investigation. Will they meet the lighthouse's infamous ghost, Ernie?

programme.title: Most Haunted: Fort Delaware
programme.desc: Fort Delaware is a huge and imposing location that once held 13,000 prisoners. With such a large area to go over, the team has their work cut out investigating the fort before sunrise.

programme.title: Most Haunted: The Southern Mansion
programme.desc: Although now a high-class bed and breakfast, the Southern Mansion still has a few residents from its past hanging around. The team explores unexplained noises, bangs and whispers in the night.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Conference House
programme.desc: The Conference House is a colonial mansion and the site of a peace conference held to stop the Revolutionary War. The team holds a séance as noises, moans and taps come from all over the house.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Speke Hall, Garston, Liverpool
programme.desc: Speke Hall's history predates the current house by hundreds of years, with evidence of former buildings in the manor walls. The team tries to summon Mary Norris, who walks the halls seeking her child.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Inveraray Jail, Argyll
programme.desc: Built in 1820, the site was home the Argyll jail and courthouse. Over 6,000 were tried and imprisoned in its eight cells. Now a museum, visitors report clanking chains and dark figures in the shadows.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Oh Lucky Man
programme.desc: Mark plans to give a recent windfall to a boys' club. But first he must deal with some con artists.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Basinger's New York
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark's assignment at Christmastime is to show a disillusioned columnist that there's still some good out there.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: All That Glitters
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark pose as priests in order to re-open an abandoned church as a shelter when a major fire breaks out in a neighborhood.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Wally
programme.desc: Wally is a hobo and street puppeteer whose caring and goodness have made him an angel without him knowing it.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Song of Songs
programme.desc: A struggling pianist tries to start life again after a heart attack.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Night to Remember
programme.desc: High school seniors hope they get the dates they want for prom.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Mother and a Daughter
programme.desc: An estranged daughter is writing a vengeful expose about her mother, a much-beloved movie star.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Age Defense
programme.desc: Katie is a stay-at-home mom who put her own aspirations on hold for her husband and kids, but now she's ready to start fresh. After a little cosmetic tweaking to perfect her smile and high-tech dermatology to help her skin, she's ready to strike back.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Sue Chamberlain
programme.desc: For the past 12 years Sue Chamberlain has been harbouring a devastating secret. She's entirely lost her confidence and her youth. Presenter Nicky Hambleton-Jones and a team of experts revive Sue's confidence.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Bringin’ Back the Lovin’ Feeling
programme.desc: As a working mom of two toddlers, Sara has no time for hairstyles and fancy clothes. She used to spend hours in the gym but now she's traded in her workout schedule for changing diapers and story time.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Life Lessons for Linda
programme.desc: Linda's a stay-at-home mom whose two sons have left the nest for college, so she's decided to go back to school as well! Not wanting to be viewed as the "Mom" on campus, Linda wants to update her appearance so she can look and feel more confident.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Truly A Trophy
programme.desc: Rapid aging as a result of early menopause left Deborah feeling stressed out and feeling anything but sexy. She is sick of spending her days in sweats and wants to feel like a woman again.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Mission: Makeover
programme.desc: Jennifer is a dedicated military wife who works hard to care for her family while her husband serves in Iraq. It's time for Jennifer to begin her own mission impossible-transforming herself into a new woman for her husband who soon returns from war.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Back in Business
programme.desc: Melissa is a busy mother of four who also runs her own online cosmetic business. But with not enough time in the day, she's stopped wearing the make up she sells and fears her aging looks will hurt her business.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: One Hot Pizza Guy To Go
programme.desc: Frank is a husband and father who has overcome hardships to start a small business of his own. But his decaying teeth give him an unwanted tough guy image because he never smiles. Frank's ready to shed the old image and start fresh.
programme.sub-title: One Hot Pizza Guy To Go

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Duty Calls
programme.desc: Kimberly met her husband in the Air Force. They lived an active lifestyle until his health forced him into a wheelchair. The stress of care giving and years of smoking has caught up to her and it's Kimberly's turn to receive some care.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Hair Today, Gone Tomorrow
programme.desc: Kim is a suburban wife and mother that never shook off the hippie-look of her youth. Now she longs for a more polished and sophisticated image than her long braid and wire-rimmed glasses.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Sue Chamberlain "One Year On"
programme.desc: Just a year ago, Sue Chamberlain was a 34 year old living in a 40 year old's body. Now, a year on, we retrace Sue's transformational journey – and pop in to pay Sue a return visit. Will she still be looking fabulous – or flabby?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Facing the Music
programme.desc: KerriAnn is a Rock n' Roll singer who has recently lost her rhythm. Years of touring with a band and the recent loss of two family members has taken its toll on her looks. Our team of experts is going to try and make KerriAnn look 10 Years Younger.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Siobhan Wirdman
programme.desc: Step in Nicky Hambleton-Jones to rescue 37 year old Siobhan Wirdman and get this full time wife and mother to love herself and get her life back on track.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Facing the Music
programme.desc: KerriAnn is a Rock n' Roll singer who has recently lost her rhythm. Years of touring with a band and the recent loss of two family members has taken its toll on her looks. Our team of experts is going to try and make KerriAnn look 10 Years Younger.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Dawn Feeling
programme.desc: At a typically rowdy family breakfast, Rosie is excitedly looking forward to the arrival of her friend Izzy, whilst Danny is concerned about the rumour of ivory poachers in the area. Unnoticed, Miranda the lion cub pads off into the bush.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 1
programme.desc: The Trevanions have been living at Leopard's Den for over a year. The wildlife is roaming freely and the family are settled into African way of life. Business however is not good. With an abundance of game lodges competition is fierce.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 2
programme.desc: It's the grand reopening of Mara and a British wildlife charity is using the event to release a vulture back into the wild. Fatani, the new, young and ambitious manager of Mara has hired Danny as the vet to oversee the release.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 3
programme.desc: Leopard's Den is looking after a sick and orphaned baby elephant called Togo. However, despite Evan and Du Plessis' constant vigil, Togo is dying from a broken heart. Evan is distraught and Du Plessis promises they will look after her together.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 4
programme.desc: Sarah's absence couldn't have come at a worse time for Leopard's Den. Nature Conservation is carrying out their annual inspection and everything has to be tip top. Danny's determined they pass with flying colours and everyone is roped in to help.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 5
programme.desc: Everyone's excited at the prospect of Leopard's Den's new arrival. Bash, Danny's old tutor and Rosie's Godfather, is coming from England to help Danny grow his veterinary practice.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 6
programme.desc: The Trevanions are delighted when Fatani asks Danny to take an aggressive hippo off his hands. As they prepare for its arrival Sarah gets a bit of a shock when her mother Caroline beats the hippo to the post.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 7
programme.desc: Business is looking up at Leopard's Den but Sarah is feeling agitated. Caroline thinks it because Simon, her ex husband and Evan and Olivia's Dad, is arriving from England to get married. But Sarah has other things on her mind.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 8
programme.desc: As a weather bomb hits, the chopper crew set out on one of the most challenging missions they have ever undertaken 20 miles off shore, a man lays face down at Muriwai beach unable to move.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 9
programme.desc: A hang glider pilot may have broken his back after a heavy crash-landing, a Manaia man is in a bad way after coming off a sea biscuit at high speed, and a crashed Waikato driver needs an urgent air-lift to hospital to save his life.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 10
programme.desc: A motocross rider may have broken his back after hitting a tree head on at high speed, at a sawmill a man faces its worse nightmares; and a woman is fighting for her life after taking an accidental overdose of her husband's medication.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 3
programme.desc: A monster swell has trapped two teenage girls on the rocks at Sydney's North Head. As high-tide approaches, a daring double-winch rescue is their only option – to stop the teenagers from being swept out to sea.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 4
programme.desc: 55-year-old Gold Coast holidaymaker Irina is in real trouble - she's caught in a deadly ocean rip. Like many tourists, Irena was unaware of the risks of not swimming between the beach flags. The Gold Coast rescue helicopter spots her in the nick of time.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: A head-on car collision in Tasmania has left tourists Hong and Xeu Wu fighting for their lives. Ambulance crews have managed to stabilize Mr. Wu but Mrs. Wu is in a critical condition and calling out for her husband.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 4
programme.desc: Jarryd's been busted for drugs in a country where they still have the death penalty. And now he plans to double-cross the Thai authorities and escape to Singapore with his pregnant girlfriend.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 5
programme.desc: Beau was left for dead by the side of a road after a horrific motorbike crash. Now he wants to discharge himself from hospital. Can the embassy stop him before he self-destructs?

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 6
programme.desc: The embassy visits a convicted drug dealer in the world's most notorious prison. But Steven claims he's the innocent victim of an undercover drug sting gone wrong.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 7
programme.desc: Young Rhys calls the embassy after his businessman father is arrested and jailed for fraud. Can Rhys raise the bail money to get him out of jail? It's a race against the clock.

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 8
programme.desc: Ash contacts the embassy convinced he's going to die after days of partying. The notorious Thai bucket strikes again! The embassy needs to uncover the truth. Is he really in danger or is he suffering from alcohol poisoning?

programme.title: The Embassy: Episode 1
programme.desc: Nathan is in Phuket on a holiday of a lifetime, fuelled by sun, sex and steroids, when disaster strikes. 19-year-old Paris is on a gap year adventure of a lifetime. But just two months into her first-ever overseas holiday she's hit a big roadblock.

programme.title: I Want My Mummy!: Episode 1
programme.desc: Pig farmer Keith and graphic designer Jonathon are about to take on the toughest job of their lives. Their worn-out wives Rosh and Natalie have gone on strike and are spending three days at a luxury spa.

programme.title: Motorvision Special: X-Raid Rally Dakar
programme.desc: Stéphane Peterhansel is the most successful driver in the history of the Dakar Rally. Along with the German team X-Raid he wins the 2012 and 2013 editions of this prestigious marathon in a Mini Countryman.

programme.title: Motorvision Special: Ice Action Finland
programme.desc: Former World Rally Champion Armin Schwarz is a legend behind the wheels. Now he is instructing other talented people in driving a 300 hp Subaru WRX STI rally car on the snowy and icy, but also breathtaking landscape of Finland.

programme.title: Motorvision Special: Racechip Challenge
programme.desc: More power and yet better fuel economy? With chip tuning this is supposed to be possible. We want to check this out and send two teams on a road trip with a difference. From Uhingen near Stuttgart in Germany, we travel to Barcelona and back.

programme.title: Motorvision Special: New Car Purchase Experience
programme.desc: A new car. A new driving experience. A new lifestyle. But which paths do four wheels, an engine and a whole lot of sheet metal take until the first drive? This is a question probably only asked by a few.

programme.title: Motorvision Special: 90 Years BMW Motor Bike
programme.desc: Precision, high-tech, high quality: After nine decades of eventful history ""BMW Motor Bikes"" are seen today are being almost too perfect. A story between tradition and innovation with ups and downs.

programme.title: Motorvision Special: The Car of the Future
programme.desc: The car of the future - this is how it might look: Aerodynamic, light and quiet. And with almost no fuel consumption. This is how we could soon travel on roads. But is a car like this just a pipe dream of engineers?

programme.title: Motorvision Special: Isle of Mann TT 2015 Documentary
programme.desc: The Tourist Trophy on the British Isle of Man is the most famous motorcycle race in the world. TT Sidecar champion Klaus Klaffenböck and racing expert Lenz Leberkern explore the fascination behind the TT Isle of Man.

programme.title: Motorvision Special: Vintage Airplane Show Days
programme.desc: In this special report Motorvision TV will not be on tour on the streets, but in the air and will pay a tribute to the history of motorized aviation. One of the oldest airfields in Germany is located at Oberschleissheim near Munich.

programme.title: Motorvision Special: Germany´s Supercar Rally
programme.desc: On Saturday the 11th of July 2015, owners and co-drivers of 450 supercars flocked at Germany's Bielefeld to join the biggest supercar rally ever organized in Europe so far.

programme.title: On Tour: Night of the Jumps
programme.desc: Munich, the Olympic Arena at the Night of the Jumps. These young guys will make the arena shake. They are fearless, and are going to really let it rip today. The biggest motor cross freestyle event in the world!

programme.title: On Tour: Bus Stunts with Action Concept
programme.desc: We are going to take you behind the scenes of the movie industry. We are here with Action Concept, Europe's most successful film production company, testing a stunt with a twelve ton bus going to be sent into the air.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Death Grip
programme.desc: When a speeding truck crashes into a residential building, officers find the lifeless body of Michael Faast behind the wheel. But he didn’t die in the wreck – he was shot point-blank in the temple.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Murder in a Bottle
programme.desc: Eric Houston is found stabbed to death in a seedy motel, but the ensuing investigation is stymied by a long list of suspects. Lt. Joe Kenda deploys a groundbreaking new technology to catch the killer.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter
programme.desc: When police find 24-year-old Patrick Ray with a gunshot to the temple, the scene has all the telltale signs of suicide. But Lt. Joe Kenda's instinct says otherwise.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Death Rains Down
programme.desc: Restaurant worker Sharon Coleman is murdered in a hail of large caliber gunfire. Kenda must break through a web of lies to hunt down one of the most dangerous criminal masterminds he’s ever faced.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Bump In the Night
programme.desc: When a pretty, young pilot is found in bed, bound and with a bullet in her head, Lt. Joe Kenda must determine if this was a random assault or payback for something that happened in the skies.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Manifesto
programme.desc: A cabin on the slopes of Pikes Peak catches fire, and a young sheriff’s deputy is posted to guard the scene overnight--then he’s found dead in his patrol car the next morning.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Knock Knock
programme.desc: A gathering of friends turns deadly when two gunmen shoot William Davis in the head. Kenda and his team dig into his past and start to suspect someone in William’s circle is lying.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Written in Blood
programme.desc: A community is shocked when Antoine McKenzie is brazenly shot outside an auto parts store in broad daylight. The only lead left for Lt. Joe Kenda is a final message written in the victim’s own blood.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Homewrecking Hounds
programme.desc: Cesar helps a newlywed couple whose dogs don't let them get close and another pair who met online and are nervous about introducing their dogs.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Woody & Wally, various dogs, and Kane
programme.desc: Cesar shows mail carriers in Roswell, Georgia, how to deal with close encounters of the four-legged kind. Next, Cesar meets a pair of Pomeranians that flip out when left alone.
programme.sub-title: Woody & Wally, various dogs, and Kane

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Woof and Wheels
programme.desc: People and their dogs descended on a local PETCO to meet producers in the hopes of a session with Cesar Millan. Meet two of the problem pooches. Can Cesar dial down the bad behavior of these terrors?

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Riley & Sophie, Aussie and Lulu, Bebe, & Sasha
programme.desc: A couple of adopted basset hounds have a bad case of sibling rivalry. A dingo mix from Australia hasn't adjusted to her new life in California. An overly protective poodle.
programme.sub-title: Riley & Sophie, Aussie and Lulu, Bebe, & Sasha

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Buddy: Red Alert
programme.desc: Pit Bull Buddy, was found chained and starving to death and was very aggressive. Rufus, a Rottweiler/Shar Pei mix, has bitten five people. Both need to get their aggression under control.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Tillie and Leo
programme.desc: A rehabilitated Wheaten Terrier mix grows overly attached to his rescuer. The owners of a Shar-pei must deal with the result of their dog’s growing aggression towards other dogs.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Bodhi, Maggie & Molly, and Bojo
programme.desc: Bloodhound/Catahoula mix, Bojo, is aggressive when it comes to mealtime. Molly and Maggie, two territorial Maltese, and a Kerry Blue Terrier in need of some calm assertive energy.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Cesar Conquers London
programme.desc: There's anarchy in the UK as Cesar faces a challenge from a rowdy Jack Russell, two culture-shocked pooches and an unruly Patterdale terrier mix.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Make-up Addict/Obsessed with Death
programme.desc: Maureen won't go out of the house without a full face of makeup. Meanwhile, Barbara is so obsessed with death that she's planned her own funeral.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Can’t Stop Cleaning/Love Rocks
programme.desc: Cyntrelle dropped out of high school because of her addiction to cleaning. Belinda's obsession with rocks has taken over her life, with more than 100,000 scattered around her home.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: My Strange Addiction Special 1
programme.desc: “My Strange Addiction” tells the story of people who just can't stop doing very strange things, including a compulsive tanner, a runner, a shopper and a chalk eater.

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: Star Chaser_The Little Merman
programme.desc: Eric is obsessed with Mermaids and has transformed himself into a real-life Merman. Vanessa is so obsessed with meeting celebrities that she spends all day searching them out.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Eats Toilet Paper/Blow Dryer
programme.desc: Lori has been sleeping with her blow dryer for 20 years, despite the risk burns or fire. Meanwhile, Kesha's family is concerned that eating half a roll of toilet paper a day is causing health issues.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Laxatives and Pottery/Ashes
programme.desc: Kimberly takes hundreds of laxatives a day in an attempt to lose weight. Meanwhile, Bianca prefers to eat pottery and cigarette ashes instead of food.

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: Ketchup_Mustard
programme.desc: Ketchup or Mustard? Barry owns the world’s largest mustard collection numbering 5,500 bottles from 80 countries. Ralph’s rare collection of Ketchup bottles includes a patent bottle from 1891.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Eats Bricks / Married To A Carnival Ride
programme.desc: For the past three years, 56-year-old Linda has been happily married to Bruce, a 70-foot carnival ride. Patrice is also happily married and showcases her addiction for eating brick.
programme.sub-title: Eats Bricks / Married To A Carnival Ride

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Addicted to Being Pamela Anderson
programme.desc: Carolyn Anderson, a 29 year-old women from the UK, is addicted to transforming herself into Baywatch beauty Pamela Anderson.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Air Freshener / Long Neck
programme.desc: In this episode we meet Evelyn, who drinks air freshener every day, and Sydney, who is obsessed with having the world's longest neck.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Older Women/ Madonna
programme.desc: 31-year-old Kyle is addicted to dating much older women, over the age of 65. Adam is intent upon becoming Madonna.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Vapor Rubs/Eats Tires
programme.desc: Danielle has been addicted to vapor rub for more than twenty years, going through more than 30 jars, inhalers and patches every week. Allison has been eating tires for the past six years.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: The Lamb/Eats Deodorant
programme.desc: Nicole has been addicted to eating deodorant for two years, consuming fifteen sticks per month. 27-year-old Audrey can't live without her stuffed lamb.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Sucker/Bodybuilder
programme.desc: Lauren was once addicted to drugs and alcohol, but now is addicted to body-building, which may have caused long term health problems. Meanwhile, Rhonda has been addicted to sucking her thumb ever since her parents divorced when she was a child.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: No Roads In
programme.desc: Dave and Wendy want a remote cabin where they can escape to the Alaskan frontier way of life, places so hidden that the only way there is by off-road vehicle and no outhouse is safe from hungry bears.

programme.title: Buying Alaska: Jaws, Claws & Beaver Fever
programme.desc: Shane and Erica want a home in the Alaskan wild, where it’s so remote, the only way in is by a monster 8-wheeler. Homeowners beware! Bears attack the properties and beavers infect the drinking water.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Hot Tubs and Gators
programme.desc: Duck, Lathan, & Flip are tired of traveling each weekend to their favorite place to enjoy bayou living. They’re willing to do anything to buy a home if they can hunt gators right out their back door.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Lakes for the Champ
programme.desc: “Catfish” Jack Clampit and his daughter, Amanda, love hand-grabbing catfish, so he and Amanda are searching for a camp that will accommodate both their families…and their appetite for catfish.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Starter Homes
programme.desc: Josh McIntire is an avid duck hunter and fisherman and he hopes to find a house where he can do just that. He’s bringing his life-long best friend, Hanna, for guidance.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Rolling on the River
programme.desc: Bryan Fassbender and Stephanie Robichaux are self described work-a-holics who just want to have a weekend houseboat on the Pearl River, and are willing to live off the grid.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Boaters Beware
programme.desc: Matt and Laurie aren’t your ordinary couple looking for a turnkey home. They love fixing places up. They look at three unusual homes on Louisiana oxbows.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Storm Deals
programme.desc: David and Jackie love bayou life in Mississippi. With their two sons away at college, they’re looking to downsize on the water. They’re looking for a fixer upper they can make their own.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Hurricane Homes
programme.desc: Jeff and Amelia Harding cruise the Mississippi Gulf Coast in search of a new house. Amelia lost her home in Katrina, so they’re scouring the coast for a house that can stand up to a hurricane.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Beaches vs. Bayous
programme.desc: CJ, who grew up on a shrimp boat in Louisiana, and Marty, from Los Angeles, are looking for a weekend getaway but can’t agree whether it will be on the bayou or the beach.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Airboat Homes
programme.desc: They’re big, loud, fast and can traverse anything. Airboats aren’t just a novelty in Louisiana, they’re essential—join the Fradellas as they search for an airboat accessible home.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Louisiana Luxury
programme.desc: Larry and Amber Douglas started a business that has become a million-dollar operation. They’re looking to upgrade their lifestyle, but still want a place with a down home bayou feel.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Cruisin For A Bruisin
programme.desc: Join Jill and Marvin as they comb Belle River for the perfect floating home—something that’ll get them back in the swamps and back to their bayou roots.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Bayou Baby
programme.desc: Chris and Jessica are going back to their roots and looking for a bayou home near Houma, Louisiana. But with a rambunctious baby, finding the perfect waterfront home can be a challenge.

programme.title: Baywatch: Swept Away
programme.desc: Mitch befriends a boy who joins junior lifeguards in hopes of escaping a brutal home life. Jessie makes a passionate play for JD. Alex auditions for “Jeopardy!”

programme.title: Baywatch: The Swimmer
programme.desc: Upset about his failed marriage to Neely, Mitch goes for a day-long tower swim along the beach and encounters problems that distract from his own, including April and Craig's May/December romance, and reluctant heroes Cody and JD.

programme.title: Baywatch: Friends Forever
programme.desc: A young, hearing-impaired girl learns a lesson in friendship when she, Mitch and Alex protect an orangutan, while Cody and Jessie deal with its abusive owner.

programme.title: Baywatch: The Edge
programme.desc: Cody puts his career, and his life, on the line when he uses a performance-enhancing supplement in hopes of making the Olympic swim team. Alex becomes the object of Mitch's rejection, and Newmie's affection.

programme.title: Baywatch: The Big Blue
programme.desc: Mitch tries to reunite an Army parachutist with her estranged Naval-officer father, while Cody helps a beautiful woman try to reach record-setting depths at a national free-diving competition.

programme.title: Baywatch: Come Fly with Me
programme.desc: After he tries to save Tanner from his abusive father, Mitch ends up on the wrong side of the law. Meanwhile, Jessie's irresistible charm makes a stunt pilot's heart take flight.

programme.title: Baywatch: Boys will be Boys
programme.desc: When caught up in a high-risk adventure at sea, Craig tells Mitch a shocking secret. Meanwhile, Jessie works to creatively end JD and Cody's rivalry during a beachside triathlon, and April comes clean with Manny.

programme.title: Baywatch: Baywatch Grand Prix
programme.desc: Mitch feels the need for speed when Tanner's cousin, Damon Lusk, a race car driver in town for a major competition, visits Baywatch. Meanwhile, Newmie and the gang develop a TV show about lifeguards that they try to sell it into syndication.

programme.title: House on Haunted Hill
programme.desc: A millionaire offers $10,000 to five people who agree to be locked in a large, spooky, rented house overnight with him and his wife.

programme.title: The Last Man on Earth
programme.desc: When a disease turns all of humanity into the living dead, the last man on earth becomes a reluctant vampire hunter.

programme.title: Halloween
programme.desc: Fifteen years after murdering his sister on Halloween night 1963, Michael Myers escapes from a mental hospital and returns to the small town of Haddonfield, Illinois to kill again. Starring: Donald Pleasence, Jamie Lee Curtis, Tony Moran

programme.title: Ghostline
programme.desc: Life takes a terrifying and unpredictable turn for Tyler & Chelsea when they begin to receive menacing phone calls from a seemingly unstable woman who insists that Tyler's her ex-boyfriend.

programme.title: The Haunting
programme.desc: A lawyer who doesn't believe in ghosts is haunted after moving into a family mansion. Starring: Tim Daly, Tom Arnold, Zoe Saldana
